		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />From <a href="http://nesdevwiki.org/wiki/APU_DMC" class="postlink">wiki</a>:
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Any time the sample buffer is in an empty state and bytes remaining is not zero, the following occur:<br /><br />    * The sample buffer is filled with the next sample byte read from the current address, subject to whatever mapping hardware is present. The CPU is suspend for four clock cycles.</div>
<br />
<br />- If the CPU is suspend for 4 cycles, what happens with the PPU/APU? Does it render background pixels (color index at 3F00), or just "skip" 16 dots? Actually, my PPU render does 16 clocks (or dots) instead of just 3.

		

		</td>
